<p>The term <b>sonic boom</b> is commonly used to refer to the shocks caused by the <a href="/wiki/Supersonic" title="Supersonic">supersonic</a> flight of an aircraft. Sonic booms generate enormous amounts of sound energy, sounding much like an <a href="/wiki/Explosion" title="Explosion">explosion</a>. <a href="/wiki/Thunder" title="Thunder">Thunder</a> is a type of natural sonic boom, created by the rapid heating and expansion of air in a <a href="/wiki/Lightning" title="Lightning">lightning</a> discharge.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
